query.result:
1 The sun had already reached the horizon 2 whose meridian circle covers 3 Jerusalem with its highest point;
4 and the night, which circles opposite to it, 5 was coming out of the Ganges with the Scales, 6 which fall from its hands when it prevails;
7 so that the white and red cheeks, 8 where I was, of the beautiful Aurora 9 were becoming orange due to old age.

